    • DataGatherer

      @MustBeClosed public DataGatherer(ProxyAwareStorage db, Machine machine) throws IOException, StorageException, SpinnmanException, InterruptedException
      Create an instance of the protocol implementation. (Subclasses handle where to put it afterwards.)
      Parameters:
      db - Database to use to get proxy information.
      machine - The description of the SpiNNaker machine being talked to.
      Throws:
      IOException - If we can't discover the machine details due to I/O problems
      InterruptedException - If communications are interrupted.
      SpinnmanException - If the there is an error creating a transceiver.
      StorageException - If the database access fails.

    • gather

      public int gather(List<Gather> gatherers) throws IOException, ProcessException, StorageException, InterruptedException
      Download he contents of the regions that are described through the data gatherers.
      Parameters:
      gatherers - The data gatherer information for the boards.
      Returns:
      The total number of missed packets. Misses are retried, so this is just an assessment of data transfer quality.
      Throws:
      IOException - If IO fails.
      ProcessException - If SpiNNaker rejects a message.
      StorageException - If DB access goes wrong.
      InterruptedException - If communications are interrupted.

    • getRecordingRegion

      @ForOverride protected abstract BufferManagerStorage.Region getRecordingRegion(Placement placement, int regionID) throws IOException, ProcessException, StorageException, InterruptedException
      Work out exactly where is going to be downloaded. The elements of the list this method returns will end up directing what calls to storeData(...) are done, and the order in which they are done.

      The recording region memory management scheme effectively requires this to be a list of zero, one or two elements, but the DataGatherer class does not care.

      Parameters:
      placement - The placement information.
      regionID - The region ID.
      Returns:
      The region descriptors that are the actual download instructions. May be unmodifiable.
      Throws:
      IOException - If communication fails.
      ProcessException - If SpiNNaker rejects a message.
      StorageException - If the database doesn't like something.
      InterruptedException - If communications are interrupted.

    • storeData

      @ForOverride protected abstract void storeData(BufferManagerStorage.Region r, ByteBuffer data) throws StorageException
      Store the data retrieved from a region No guarantee is made about which thread will call this method.
      Parameters:
      r - Where the data came from.
      data - The data that was retrieved.
      Throws:
      StorageException - If the database refuses to do the store.
